		<h2>Undergraduate Financial Support</h2>
		<p>The School of Integrative Biology is pleased to offer the following awards to undergraduates majoring in Integrative Biology or Integrative Biology Honors. Most of these awards have been made possible by generous donations by friends of the School.</p>
		<p>Full descriptions and eligibility requirements of all awards are provided below.&nbsp; To apply for one or more award, compile all required material into a single PDF and submit to <a href="mailto:sibundergrad@life.illinois.edu">sibundergrad@life.illinois.edu</a>.</p>
		<p><strong><a href="http://sib.illinois.edu/SIB%20UG%20Awards%202015.docx" target="_blank">Application</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>Deadline</strong> for receipt of applications is <strong>midnight on Monday, March 9, 2015</strong>. Please direct any questions to <a href="mailto:sibundergrad@life.illinois.edu">sibundergrad@life.illinois.edu</a>.</p>

		<h3>1) Mildred Parizek Zukor Award ($450) </h3>
		<p>Description: This award, made possible by the donor and her family, recognizes outstanding achievement in undergraduate research in Animal Biology or Zoology.</p>
		<p><strong>Eligibility</strong></p>
		<ul class="ul_list">
			<li>Current Juniors or Seniors</li>
			<li>At least one completed semester of IB 390 or 490</li>
			<li>Plans to continue as a graduate student on the UIUC campus</li>
			<li>Letter of reference from research advisor</li>
		</ul><hr>
		 <h3>2) Dr. A. Malmed Award ($750) </h3>
		<p>Description:<strong>This award, which will only be available in 2015, was provided by an alumnus providing leadership in the health field.</strong></p>
		<p><strong>Eligibility</strong></p>
		<ul class="ul_list">
			<li>Current Juniors</li>
			<li>Outstanding service and / or leadership</li>
			<li>Vision for future service or leadership</li>
		</ul><hr>

